            <!-- Welcome Tab -->
            <div id="welcome" class="tab-container active" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="tab-welcome">
                <section class="section section-complete">
                    <h2><i class="fas fa-leaf" aria-hidden="true"></i> Welcome to AHCPCM303: Identify Plant Specimens</h2>
                    
                    <h3>Overview of Plant Identification</h3>
                    <p>Welcome to the fascinating world of plant identification! This unit will equip you with the essential skills to accurately identify plant specimens using a range of techniques and resources. Whether you're working in conservation, land management, horticulture, or environmental consulting, the ability to correctly identify plants is fundamental to your role.</p>
                    
                    <div class="key-point">
                        <div class="key-point-title"><i class="fas fa-lightbulb" aria-hidden="true"></i> Why Plant Identification Matters in Tasmania</div>
                        <p>Tasmania is home to over 2,300 native vascular plant species, with approximately 580 species (25%) being endemic to the state. From the ancient Gondwanan rainforests to the unique alpine ecosystems, accurate identification is crucial for conservation, weed management, and ecological restoration.</p>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="flashcard-set">
                        <div class="flashcard-set-title">Tasmanian Flora Facts Flashcards</div>
                        
                        <div class="flashcard-container" id="welcome-card-1">
                            <div class="flashcard" onclick="flipCard('welcome-card-1')" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-label="Flashcard: How many native vascular plant species occur in Tasmania? Press enter to flip." onkeypress="if(event.key==='Enter') flipCard('welcome-card-1')">
                                <div class="flashcard-front">
                                    <h3>How many native vascular plant species occur in Tasmania?</h3>
                                </div>
                                <div class="flashcard-back">
                                    <p>Approximately 2,300 native vascular plant species, with around 580 species (25%) being endemic to Tasmania.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="flashcard-nav">
                                <button class="nav-button" onclick="flipCard('welcome-card-1')" aria-label="Flip current flashcard"><i class="fas fa-sync-alt" aria-hidden="true"></i> Flip Card</button>
                                <button class="nav-button" onclick="showNextCard('welcome', 1)" aria-label="Show next flashcard"><i class="fas fa-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"></i> Next</button>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        
                        <div class="flashcard-container" id="welcome-card-2" style="display:none;">
                            <div class="flashcard" onclick="flipCard('welcome-card-2')" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-label="Flashcard: What is Tasmania's floral emblem? Press enter to flip." onkeypress="if(event.key==='Enter') flipCard('welcome-card-2')">
                                <div class="flashcard-front">
                                    <h3>What is Tasmania's floral emblem?</h3>
                                </div>
                                <div class="flashcard-back">
                                    <p>The Tasmanian Blue Gum (<em>Eucalyptus globulus</em>) was proclaimed as the state's floral emblem in 1962.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="flashcard-nav">
                                <button class="nav-button" onclick="showPrevCard('welcome', 2)" aria-label="Show previous flashcard"><i class="fas fa-arrow-left" aria-hidden="true"></i> Previous</button>
                                <button class="nav-button" onclick="flipCard('welcome-card-2')" aria-label="Flip current flashcard"><i class="fas fa-sync-alt" aria-hidden="true"></i> Flip Card</button>
