                    </div>
                    
                    <h3>Unit Elements and Performance Criteria</h3>
                    <p>This unit covers the following key elements:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Element 1:</strong> Prepare for plant identification activities</li>
                        <li><strong>Element 2:</strong> Observe and record plant features</li>
                        <li><strong>Element 3:</strong> Use identification resources</li>
                        <li><strong>Element 4:</strong> Document and report identification outcomes</li>
                    </ul>
                    
                    <h3>How to Use This Resource</h3>
                    <p>This comprehensive learning resource includes:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>10 detailed sections with 500-800 words of original content each</li>
                        <li>100+ interactive flashcards and specimen cards</li>
                        <li>50+ self-assessment questions with immediate feedback</li>
                        <li>5-10 dichotomous key simulations</li>
                        <li>Complete database of 100+ Tasmanian native species</li>
                        <li>30+ threatened species profiles with EPBC and TAS Act status</li>
                        <li>3 full practice exams with model answers</li>
                        <li>Progress tracking and save/load functionality</li>
                    </ul>
                </section>
                
