            <!-- Section 1: Plant Classification -->
            <div id="section1" class="tab-container" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="tab-section1">
                <section class="section">
                    <h2><i class="fas fa-sitemap" aria-hidden="true"></i> Section 1: Plant Classification</h2>
                    
                    <h3>Taxonomic Hierarchy with Tasmanian Examples</h3>
                    <p>The taxonomic hierarchy provides a structured way to classify and name plants based on their evolutionary relationships. From broadest to most specific, the levels are:</p>
                    
                    <div class="table-container">
                        <table>
                            <caption>Taxonomic hierarchy levels with descriptions and Tasmanian examples</caption>
                            <thead>
                                <tr>
                                    <th scope="col">Rank</th>
                                    <th scope="col">Description</th>
                                    <th scope="col">Tasmanian Example</th>
                                </tr>
                            </thead>
                            <tbody>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>Domain</td>
                                    <td>Eukarya (all organisms with membrane-bound nuclei)</td>
                                    <td>All Tasmanian plants</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>Kingdom</td>
                                    <td>Plantae (photosynthetic, multicellular)</td>
                                    <td>All Tasmanian native plants</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>Division (Phylum)</td>
                                    <td>Major evolutionary lineage (e.g., Angiosperms, Gymnosperms)</td>
                                    <td>Magnoliophyta (flowering plants)</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>Class</td>
                                    <td>Within division, based on major structural features</td>
                                    <td>Magnoliopsida (dicots) or Liliopsida (monocots)</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>Order</td>
                                    <td>Group of related families</td>
                                    <td>Myrtales (includes Myrtaceae family)</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>Family</td>
                                    <td>Group of related genera</td>
                                    <td>Myrtaceae (eucalypts, tea-trees)</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>Genus</td>
                                    <td>Group of closely related species</td>
                                    <td><em>Eucalyptus</em></td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>Species</td>
                                    <td>Basic unit of classification, capable of interbreeding</td>
                                    <td><em>Eucalyptus globulus</em> (Tasmanian Blue Gum)</td>
                                </tr>
                            </tbody>
                        </table>
                    </div>
                    
                    <h3>Binomial Nomenclature Rules with 20+ Tasmanian Examples</h3>
                    <p>Binomial nomenclature, developed by Carl Linnaeus, gives each species a unique two-part scientific name:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Genus</strong> (capitalized) + <strong>species epithet</strong> (lowercase), both italicized or underlined</li>
                        <li>When handwritten, underline separately: <u>Eucalyptus</u> <u>globulus</u></li>
                        <li>Always include the author citation in formal contexts (e.g., <em>Eucalyptus globulus</em> Labill.)</li>
                    </ul>
                    
                    <div class="activity-box">
                        <div class="activity-title"><i class="fas fa-tag" aria-hidden="true"></i> 25+ Tasmanian Species Examples (Corrected Classifications)</div>
                        <div class="specimen-grid" style="display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 0.5rem;">
                            <span class="specimen-card" style="width: auto; padding: 0.5rem;"><em>Eucalyptus globulus</em> (Myrtaceae)</span>
                            <span class="specimen-card" style="width: auto; padding: 0.5rem;"><em>Nothofagus cunninghamii</em> (Nothofagaceae)</span>
                            <span class="specimen-card" style="width: auto; padding: 0.5rem;"><em>Athrotaxis selaginoides</em> (Cupressaceae)</span>
                            <span class="specimen-card" style="width: auto; padding: 0.5rem;"><em>Telopea truncata</em> (Proteaceae)</span>
                            <span class="specimen-card" style="width: auto; padding: 0.5rem;"><em>Richea pandanifolia</em> (Ericaceae)</span>
                            <span class="specimen-card" style="width: auto; padding: 0.5rem;"><em>Dicksonia antarctica</em> (Dicksoniaceae)</span>
                            <span class="specimen-card" style="width: auto; padding: 0.5rem;"><em>Lagarostrobos franklinii</em> (Podocarpaceae)</span>
                            <span class="specimen-card" style="width: auto; padding: 0.5rem;"><em>Pomaderris apetala</em> (Rhamnaceae)</span>
                            <span class="specimen-card" style="width: auto; padding: 0.5rem;"><em>Bedfordia salicina</em> (Asteraceae)</span>
                            <span class="specimen-card" style="width: auto; padding: 0.5rem;"><em>Anopterus glandulosus</em> (Escalloniaceae)</span>
                            <span class="specimen-card" style="width: auto; padding: 0.5rem;"><em>Cenarrhenes nitida</em> (Proteaceae)</span>
                            <span class="specimen-card" style="width: auto; padding: 0.5rem;"><em>Atherosperma moschatum</em> (Atherospermataceae)</span>
                            <span class="specimen-card" style="width: auto; padding: 0.5rem;"><em>Phyllocladus aspleniifolius</em> (Podocarpaceae)</span>
                            <span class="specimen-card" style="width: auto; padding: 0.5rem;"><em>Orites diversifolia</em> (Proteaceae)</span>
                            <span class="specimen-card" style="width: auto; padding: 0.5rem;"><em>Lomatia tinctoria</em> (Proteaceae)</span>
                            <span class="specimen-card" style="width: auto; padding: 0.5rem;"><em>Epacris impressa</em> (Ericaceae)</span>
                            <span class="specimen-card" style="width: auto; padding: 0.5rem;"><em>Gahnia grandis</em> (Cyperaceae)</span>
                            <span class="specimen-card" style="width: auto; padding: 0.5rem;"><em>Poa labillardierei</em> (Poaceae)</span>
                            <span class="specimen-card" style="width: auto; padding: 0.5rem;"><em>Eucalyptus regnans</em> (Myrtaceae)</span>
                            <span class="specimen-card" style="width: auto; padding: 0.5rem;"><em>Eucalyptus delegatensis</em> (Myrtaceae)</span>
                            <span class="specimen-card" style="width: auto; padding: 0.5rem;"><em>Nothofagus gunnii</em> (Nothofagaceae)</span>
                            <span class="specimen-card" style="width: auto; padding: 0.5rem;"><em>Microcachrys tetragona</em> (Podocarpaceae)</span>
                            <span class="specimen-card" style="width: auto; padding: 0.5rem;"><em>Diselma archeri</em> (Cupressaceae)</span>
                            <span class="specimen-card" style="width: auto; padding: 0.5rem;"><em>Olearia argophylla</em> (Asteraceae)</span>
                            <span class="specimen-card" style="width: auto; padding: 0.5rem;"><em>Tasmannia lanceolata</em> (Winteraceae)</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <h3>Major Plant Divisions Present in Tasmania</h3>
                    <div class="table-container">
                        <table>
                            <caption>Major plant divisions in Tasmania with characteristics and examples</caption>
                            <thead>
                                <tr>
                                    <th scope="col">Division</th>
                                    <th scope="col">Common Name</th>
                                    <th scope="col">Characteristics</th>
                                    <th scope="col">Tasmanian Examples</th>
                                </tr>
                            </thead>
                            <tbody>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>Magnoliophyta (Angiosperms)</td>
                                    <td>Flowering plants</td>
                                    <td>Produce flowers and fruits, seeds enclosed in ovary</td>
                                    <td><em>Eucalyptus, Nothofagus, Telopea, Richea</em></td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>Pinophyta (Gymnosperms)</td>
                                    <td>Conifers</td>
                                    <td>Naked seeds in cones, needle or scale-like leaves</td>
                                    <td><em>Athrotaxis, Lagarostrobos, Microcachrys, Diselma, Phyllocladus</em></td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>Pteridophyta</td>
                                    <td>Ferns</td>
                                    <td>Vascular plants reproducing via spores, no seeds</td>
                                    <td><em>Dicksonia, Polystichum, Blechnum, Histiopteris</em></td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>Lycopodiophyta</td>
                                    <td>Clubmosses</td>
                                    <td>Small vascular plants with microphylls, spore-bearing</td>
                                    <td><em>Lycopodium, Selaginella, Huperzia</em></td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>Bryophyta</td>
                                    <td>Mosses</td>
                                    <td>Non-vascular plants, require moisture for reproduction</td>
                                    <td><em>Dawsonia, Hypnum, Sphagnum, Andreaea</em></td>
                                </tr>
                            </tbody>
                        </table>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="activity-box">
                        <div class="activity-title"><i class="fas fa-puzzle-piece" aria-hidden="true"></i> Interactive Matching Game: Match 20 Species to Their Families</div>
                        <div class="quiz-container">
                            <p>Click on the family that matches each species:</p>
                            
                            <div class="question-container">
                                <div class="question-number">Species 1: <em>Eucalyptus globulus</em></div>
                                <div class="quiz-actions" style="justify-content: flex-start;">
                                    <button class="quiz-action-button" onclick="checkFamilyMatch('Eucalyptus globulus', 'Myrtaceae')" aria-label="Select Myrtaceae for Eucalyptus globulus">Myrtaceae</button>
                                    <button class="quiz-action-button" onclick="checkFamilyMatch('Eucalyptus globulus', 'Proteaceae')" aria-label="Select Proteaceae for Eucalyptus globulus">Proteaceae</button>
                                    <button class="quiz-action-button" onclick="checkFamilyMatch('Eucalyptus globulus', 'Nothofagaceae')" aria-label="Select Nothofagaceae for Eucalyptus globulus">Nothofagaceae</button>
                                </div>
                                <div id="match-feedback-1" class="status-message" role="alert" aria-live="polite"></div>
                            </div>
                            
