            <!-- Section 2: Leaf Morphology -->
            <div id="section2" class="tab-container" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="tab-section2">
                <section class="section">
                    <h2><i class="fas fa-leaf" aria-hidden="true"></i> Section 2: Leaf Morphology</h2>
                    
                    <h3>50+ Leaf Terms with Tasmanian Examples</h3>
                    <p>Understanding leaf morphology is fundamental to plant identification. Leaves vary in arrangement, shape, margin, venation, and surface characteristics.</p>
                    
                    <div class="table-container">
                        <table>
                            <caption>Comprehensive leaf morphology terms with Tasmanian examples</caption>
                            <thead>
                                <tr>
                                    <th scope="col">Category</th>
                                    <th scope="col">Term</th>
                                    <th scope="col">Description</th>
                                    <th scope="col">Tasmanian Example</th>
                                </tr>
                            </thead>
                            <tbody>
                                <tr><td>Arrangement</td><td>Alternate</td><td>Leaves arranged singly at nodes</td><td><em>Eucalyptus globulus</em> (adult)</td></tr>
                                <tr><td>Arrangement</td><td>Opposite</td><td>Leaves in pairs at nodes</td><td><em>Nothofagus cunninghamii</em></td></tr>
                                <tr><td>Arrangement</td><td>Whorled</td><td>Three or more leaves at a node</td><td><em>Acacia verticillata</em></td></tr>
                                <tr><td>Arrangement</td><td>Rosulate</td><td>Leaves in a basal rosette</td><td><em>Astelia alpina</em></td></tr>
                                <tr><td>Shape</td><td>Lanceolate</td><td>Lance-shaped, broader at base</td><td><em>Eucalyptus globulus</em> (juvenile)</td></tr>
                                <tr><td>Shape</td><td>Ovate</td><td>Egg-shaped, broader at base</td><td><em>Nothofagus cunninghamii</em></td></tr>
                                <tr><td>Shape</td><td>Linear</td><td>Long and narrow with parallel sides</td><td><em>Richea sprengelioides</em></td></tr>
                                <tr><td>Shape</td><td>Cordate</td><td>Heart-shaped</td><td><em>Anodopetalum biglandulosum</em></td></tr>
                                <tr><td>Shape</td><td>Obovate</td><td>Egg-shaped, broader at tip</td><td><em>Pomaderris apetala</em></td></tr>
                                <tr><td>Shape</td><td>Falcate</td><td>Sickle-shaped</td><td><em>Eucalyptus obliqua</em></td></tr>
                                <tr><td>Shape</td><td>Acicular</td><td>Needle-shaped</td><td><em>Microcachrys tetragona</em></td></tr>
                                <tr><td>Shape</td><td>Orbicular</td><td>Circular</td><td><em>Gunnera cordifolia</em></td></tr>
                                <tr><td>Shape</td><td>Deltoid</td><td>Triangular</td><td><em>Populus nigra</em> (introduced)</td></tr>
                                <tr><td>Margin</td><td>Entire</td><td>Smooth, untoothed margin</td><td><em>Atherosperma moschatum</em></td></tr>
                                <tr><td>Margin</td><td>Serrate</td><td>Saw-toothed margin</td><td><em>Orites diversifolia</em></td></tr>
                                <tr><td>Margin</td><td>Crenate</td><td>Rounded teeth</td><td><em>Bedfordia salicina</em></td></tr>
                                <tr><td>Margin</td><td>Dentate</td><td>Teeth pointing outward</td><td><em>Hedycarya angustifolia</em></td></tr>
                                <tr><td>Margin</td><td>Revolute</td><td>Margins rolled under</td><td><em>Richea pandanifolia</em></td></tr>
                                <tr><td>Margin</td><td>Involute</td><td>Margins rolled upward</td><td><em>Xanthorrhoea australis</em></td></tr>
                                <tr><td>Margin</td><td>Sinuate</td><td>Wavy margin</td><td><em>Polystichum proliferum</em></td></tr>
                                <tr><td>Margin</td><td>Lobed</td><td>Deeply indented</td><td><em>Lomatia tinctoria</em></td></tr>
                                <tr><td>Venation</td><td>Pinnate</td><td>One midrib with lateral veins</td><td><em>Nothofagus cunninghamii</em></td></tr>
                                <tr><td>Venation</td><td>Parallel</td><td>Veins parallel to each other</td><td><em>Gahnia grandis</em></td></tr>
                                <tr><td>Venation</td><td>Palmate</td><td>Veins radiating from base</td><td><em>Geranium potentilloides</em></td></tr>
                                <tr><td>Venation</td><td>Reticulate</td><td>Net-like venation</td><td><em>Atherosperma moschatum</em></td></tr>
                                <tr><td>Surface</td><td>Glabrous</td><td>Smooth, hairless</td><td><em>Eucalyptus globulus</em></td></tr>
                                <tr><td>Surface</td><td>Tomentose</td><td>Densely hairy</td><td><em>Bedfordia salicina</em></td></tr>
                                <tr><td>Surface</td><td>Glaucous</td><td>Covered with waxy bloom</td><td><em>Eucalyptus coccifera</em></td></tr>
                                <tr><td>Surface</td><td>Pubescent</td><td>Soft short hairs</td><td><em>Pomaderris apetala</em></td></tr>
                                <tr><td>Surface</td><td>Villous</td><td>Long soft hairs</td><td><em>Celmisia asteliifolia</em></td></tr>
                                <tr><td>Surface</td><td>Scabrous</td><td>Rough to touch</td><td><em>Boronia pilosa</em></td></tr>
                                <tr><td>Surface</td><td>Rugose</td><td>Wrinkled</td><td><em>Olearia rugosa</em></td></tr>
                                <tr><td>Compound</td><td>Pinnate</td><td>Leaflets arranged along a central axis</td><td><em>Polystichum proliferum</em></td></tr>
                                <tr><td>Compound</td><td>Bipinnate</td><td>Twice divided pinnately</td><td><em>Acacia dealbata</em></td></tr>
                                <tr><td>Compound</td><td>Palmate</td><td>Leaflets radiating from one point</td><td><em>Lomatia tinctoria</em></td></tr>
                                <tr><td>Compound</td><td>Trifoliolate</td><td>Three leaflets</td><td><em>Zieria arborescens</em></td></tr>
                                <tr><td>Special</td><td>Peltate</td><td>Leaf stalk attached to center</td><td><em>Hydrocotyle hirta</em></td></tr>
                                <tr><td>Special</td><td>Perfoliate</td><td>Stem appears to pass through leaf</td><td><em>Bursaria spinosa</em> (juvenile)</td></tr>
                                <tr><td>Special</td><td>Cladode</td><td>Stem modified as leaf</td><td><em>Phyllocladus aspleniifolius</em></td></tr>
                                <tr><td>Special</td><td>Phyllode</td><td>Petiole modified as leaf</td><td><em>Acacia melanoxylon</em></td></tr>
                            </tbody>
                        </table>
                        <p><em>Additional terms: elliptic, spathulate, runcinate, cleft, parted, undulate, ciliate, glandular, sessile, petiolate, sheathing, amplexicaul, decurrent, pungent, mucronate, acuminate, obtuse, truncate, emarginate.</em></p>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="flashcard-set">
                        <div class="flashcard-set-title">Leaf Morphology Flashcards</div>
                        
                        <div class="flashcard-container" id="leaf-card-1">
                            <div class="flashcard" onclick="flipCard('leaf-card-1')" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-label="Flashcard: Lanceolate leaf shape" onkeypress="if(event.key==='Enter') flipCard('leaf-card-1')">
                                <div class="flashcard-front">
                                    <h3>Lanceolate</h3>
                                </div>
                                <div class="flashcard-back">
                                    <p>Lance-shaped, broader at the base and tapering to the tip. Example: Juvenile <em>Eucalyptus globulus</em> leaves.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="flashcard-nav">
                                <button class="nav-button" onclick="flipCard('leaf-card-1')"><i class="fas fa-sync-alt" aria-hidden="true"></i> Flip Card</button>
                                <button class="nav-button" onclick="showNextCard('leaf', 1)"><i class="fas fa-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"></i> Next</button>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        
                        <div class="flashcard-container" id="leaf-card-2" style="display:none;">
                            <div class="flashcard" onclick="flipCard('leaf-card-2')" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-label="Flashcard: Revolute leaf margin" onkeypress="if(event.key==='Enter') flipCard('leaf-card-2')">
                                <div class="flashcard-front">
                                    <h3>Revolute</h3>
                                </div>
                                <div class="flashcard-back">
                                    <p>Leaf margins rolled under. Example: <em>Richea pandanifolia</em> leaves, an adaptation to reduce water loss in alpine environments.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="flashcard-nav">
                                <button class="nav-button" onclick="showPrevCard('leaf', 2)"><i class="fas fa-arrow-left" aria-hidden="true"></i> Previous</button>
                                <button class="nav-button" onclick="flipCard('leaf-card-2')"><i class="fas fa-sync-alt" aria-hidden="true"></i> Flip Card</button>
                                <button class="nav-button" onclick="showNextCard('leaf', 2)"><i class="fas fa-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"></i> Next</button>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        
                        <div class="flashcard-container" id="leaf-card-3" style="display:none;">
                            <div class="flashcard" onclick="flipCard('leaf-card-3')" role="button" tabindex="0" aria-label="Flashcard: Phyllode" onkeypress="if(event.key==='Enter') flipCard('leaf-card-3')">
                                <div class="flashcard-front">
                                    <h3>Phyllode</h3>
                                </div>
                                <div class="flashcard-back">
                                    <p>A flattened petiole that functions as a leaf. Example: <em>Acacia melanoxylon</em> (Blackwood) has phyllodes instead of true leaves.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="flashcard-nav">
                                <button class="nav-button" onclick="showPrevCard('leaf', 3)"><i class="fas fa-arrow-left" aria-hidden="true"></i> Previous</button>
