    { term: "Androecium", pronunciation: "an-dree-see-um", definition: "The male reproductive organs of a flower; the collective term for stamens.", example: "Eucalyptus flowers have numerous stamens forming the showy part of the flower." },
    { term: "Annual", pronunciation: "an-yoo-al", definition: "A plant that completes its life cycle from germination to seed production within one growing season and then dies.", example: "Many Tasmanian native herbs are annuals." },
    { term: "Anther", pronunciation: "an-ther", definition: "The pollen-bearing part of a stamen, usually borne on a filament.", example: "Telopea truncata anthers are hidden within the floral tube." },
    { term: "Apetalous", pronunciation: "a-pet-a-lus", definition: "Lacking petals.", example: "Nothofagus flowers are apetalous, with reduced perianth." },
